aa(lp40
VSo now, all of this indicates that there are molecular programs underlying biology,
p41
aVand it shows the power of molecular programs \u2014 biology does.
p42
aVAnd what I want to do is write molecular programs,
p43
aVpotentially to build technology.
p44
aVAnd there are a lot of people doing this,
p45
aVa lot of synthetic biologists doing this, like Craig Venter.
p46
aVAnd they concentrate on using cells.
p47
aVThey're cell-oriented.
p48
aVSo my friends, molecular programmers, and I
p49
aVhave a sort of biomolecule-centric approach.
p50
aVWe're interested in using DNA, RNA and protein,
p51
aVand building new languages for building things from the bottom up,
p52
aVusing biomolecules,
p53
aVpotentially having nothing to do with biology.
p54
aVSo, these are all the machines in a cell.
p55
aVThere's a camera.
p56
aVThere's the solar panels of the cell,
p57
aVsome switches that turn your genes on and off,
p58
aVthe girders of the cell, motors that move your muscles.
