aa(lp66
VIf we succeed, what will molecular programming look like?
p67
aVYou're going to sit in front of your computer.
p68
aVYou're going to design something like a cell phone,
p69
aVand in a high-level language, you'll describe that cell phone.
p70
aVThen you're going to have a compiler
p71
aVthat's going to take that description
p72
aVand it's going to turn it into actual molecules
p73
aVthat can be sent to a synthesizer
p74
aVand that synthesizer will pack those molecules into a seed.
p75
aVAnd what happens if you water and feed that seed appropriately,
p76
aVis it will do a developmental computation,
p77
aVa molecular computation, and it'll build an electronic computer.
p78
aVAnd if I haven't revealed my prejudices already,
p79
aVI think that life has been about molecular computers
p80
aVbuilding electrochemical computers,
p81
aVbuilding electronic computers,
p82
aVwhich together with electrochemical computers
p83
aVwill build new molecular computers,
p84
aVwhich will build new electronic computers, and so forth.
