aa(lp230
VAnd what's really neat about it \u2014
p231
aVwell, actually, this all looks like nano-artwork,
p232
aVbut it turns out that nano-artwork
p233
aVis just what you need to make nano-circuits.
p234
aVSo, you can put circuit components on the staples,
p235
aVlike a light bulb and a light switch.
p236
aVLet the thing assemble, and you'll get some kind of a circuit.
p237
aVAnd then you can maybe wash the DNA away and have the circuit left over.
p238
aVSo, this is what some colleagues of mine at Caltech did.
p239
aVThey took a DNA origami, organized some carbon nano-tubes,
p240
aVmade a little switch, you see here, wired it up,
p241
aVtested it and showed that it is indeed a switch.
p242
aVNow, this is just a single switch
p243
aVand you need half a billion for a computer, so we have a long way to go.
p244
aVBut this is very promising
p245
aVbecause the origami can organize parts just one-tenth the size
p246
aVof those in a normal computer.
p247
aVSo it's very promising for making small computers.
